INSTANT BBL FAQ 

🍒 How does it work? 
— Our non-surgical BBL is a minimally invasive way to plump, fill, volumize & share your booty (and hips)! It is a non-surgical alternative to a traditional Brazilian Butt Lift. 

🍒 How many syringes can I get? 
— Up to 20 in one visit

🍒 How many treatments will I need? 
— Most patients receive 1-3 treatments! It just depends on how plump you are trying to be! 

🍒 When will my results kick in? 
— You will notice some results instantly and they will continue to develop over the next 6-12 weeks. 

🍒 What if I’m interested but not 100% sure? 
— Book a virtual consultation with Helen - no pressure. 

🍒 If I book a consultation, can I receive treatment the SAME DAY? 
— Yes

Hey ladies and gents👋🏼 I wanted to reintroduce myself. My name is Helen Zhang and I am a board certified Physician Associate and a Master Aesthetic Injector at @charettecosmetics. 

I specialize in full facial balancing to enhance your natural beauty and body treatments such as penis filler and non surgical instant BBLs. 

A little bit about my own aesthetic journey - I started injectables at the age of 24 focusing on skin treatments such as microneedling with PRP and preventative botox for migraines and bruxism (teeth grinding). Since then, I get preventative botox every 3 months, facial fillers twice a year, microneedling and other skin treatments monthly by my skin team (@shainajadeskin @aestheticianbae @touched_by_tacha @porestar) In order to age gracefully, I always say it’s a marathon and not a sprint.

Some personal facts about myself:
- I am a huge yogi and was a yoga instructor in my previous life
- I have a 3 year old goldendoodle named Clark who is my whole world 
- My favorite country that I have traveled to is Spain. I spent 6 weeks there stuffing my face with tapas & sangria and it was glorious 🤤

Follow my stories for more before & after content. Can’t wait to see y’all in office soon 🫶

Sometimes a natural hip dip correction is all we need to increase that waist to hip ratio🤗

Hip dips are completely normal! They are naturally occurring inward curves and are a part of our BONY STRUCTURE - meaning you can not work out hip dips. If you have them, you have them. Gaining/losing weight and even working out will not change them due to your body's natural bone structure. If they do bother you though, my nonsurgical instant BBL technique can help you create a curvier & more pear shaped silhouette.

What an absolutely amazing weekend it was! I had the privilege of attending AIA's @injection_anatomy Advanced Cadaver Course at the @grandhyattatlanta. 
This course emphasized the importance of safe and confident injections, which can only be achieved through a profound comprehension of facial anatomy. Through an immersive cadaver dissection lab, we had the incredible opportunity to explore beneath the skin's surface. In this lab, we skillfully injected dyed filler into our cadaver and dissected to reveal a cross-sectional view of the anatomy. This hands-on experience provided me with a comprehensive understanding of the underlying structures and the potential variabilities that may arise among patients. 
Continuing my education is paramount in ensuring the utmost safety for my patients!

Thank you @dr.chrissurek, @aestheticclinique, @anitawolfrn_lipqueen, and @hookedonfillers for sharing so much knowledge over the past 2 days!

🚫 Avoid Blood Thinners: Before your appointment, skip aspirin, ibuprofen, biotin, and alcohol to reduce the risk of bruising.

📅 Plan Ahead: Schedule your treatment at least two weeks before any major events. This gives your skin time to settle and the full effects to shine through.

🗨️ Ask Away: Got questions? Your practitioner is there to help. Clear any doubts and discuss your expectations.

Follow these tips for a smooth Botox and filler experience and step into your appointment with confidence!
